# Clean code principles

Applies to `src/` simulators and DTOs. Complements `csharp-naming`, `csharp-formatting`, `core-boundaries`.

## Single responsibility

One reason to change per class/method. Split simulators by domain (damage, reveal, retreat) — not one `GameRules` god type.

## DRY

One formula, one owner in Core. Runtime/UI read computed state — do not duplicate combat math for display.

**Rule of three** before abstracting.

## KISS / YAGNI

No generic framework for one call site. Smallest correct simulator wins.

## Fix causes

Trace why bad state exists before null-guards at call sites.

## Consistency

Match existing `src/` patterns in the folder you touch. Mirror stays aligned with game Core — do not invent divergent style here.
